<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>put one’s foot down • put one’s foot to the floor</xh5><p> <i>put one’s foot down</i>—(coll.) 1. take up a firm stand on an issue: One of the best things Pope John Paul II has done is to <u>put his foot down</u> about women priests. 2. <i>(also: put one’s foot on it)</i> accelerate when driving a car: I <u>put my foot down</u> and the Zephyr gathered speed up the slope.</p><p> <i>put one’s foot to the floor</i>— = put one’s foot down 2: Jerome jerked the steering wheel hard while <u>putting his foot to the floor</u>.</p><p> <i>See also: get one’s feet under the table / put one’s feet up.</i></p> </entry>
